Comments in JS
Part of Code which is not executed

// This is a single line comment

/* This is a multi-line comment. */

Operators in JS
used to perform some operation on daa
Arithmetic Operators
-,+,*,/

-Modulus  =  %
-Exponentiation = **
-Increment = a++ = a+1
-Decrement = a-- = a-1 

a++ (post Increment)  a-- (post Decrement)
++a (pre Increment)   b++ (pre Decrement)

Assignment Operators
=, +=, -=, *=, %=, **=

Comparison operators 

Equal to ==             Equal to & type ===
Not equal to !=         Not equal to & type !==

>, >=, <, <=

Logical Operators

Logical AND &&
Logical OR ||
Logical Not !

false or true

Conditional Statements
To implement some condition in the code

if Statement

let color;
if (mod === "dark-mode") {
    color = "black";
}

if-else Statement

let color;
if (mode === "dark-mode") {
    color = "black";
} else{
    color = "white";
}

Ternary Operators 

condition ? true output: false output

age > 18 ? "adult" : "not adult";

